          "The high-speed ascent: The Xima Pool cable car is a two-stage journey. You cross through three distinct climate zones: the subtropical valley, the sub-alpine forest of hemlock and fir, and finally the alpine meadow zone where temperatures can be 15°C lower than the town.",
          "The jade belt path: A marvel of engineering, this 18km stone-paved walkway contours around the mountain at a steady 2,550m. It is perfectly flat, allowing for an effortless hike through the clouds. Along the way, you cross the mouths of the 18 streams, where waterfalls plunge into deep mountain pools.",
          "Zhaozhou Temple: Hidden in the middle slopes, this ancient temple is famous for its 'God of Wealth' shrine, favored by local merchants before they embarked on the Tea Horse Road caravans."
