          "Enclosed by ancient stone walls, the Old Town is a grid of cobblestone streets fed by clear mountain streams. While the main arterial roads (Fuxing and Renmin) are bustling with trade, the true character of Dali is found in the hidden corners. The town has been the political heart of Yunnan for over 500 years, serving as the capital of the Nanzhao and Dali Kingdoms.",
          "Venture west towards the Cangshan foothills to find the 'lower city' atmosphere, where artisans still hammer copper and old women in indigo headscarves sell wild mushrooms. The preservation of the Ming-style architecture, with its distinctive 'three-over-one' roofs, makes every alleyway a potential discovery for the patient traveller.",
          "A unique fusion of Gothic architecture and traditional Bai motifs. The wooden interior and white-and-grey screen-wall facade are architectural marvels.",
          "Located near the North Gate, this rooftop spot offers the best coffee in town with uninterrupted views of Cangshan.",
          "Avoid the tourist crowds on Fuxing and head to the lower end of Renmin Road for independent bookstores, vinyl shops, and craft beer bars.",
