          "Xizhou is a sanctuary for traditional Bai residential architecture, preserving over 100 Ming and Qing dynasty dwellings. These homes are defined by sophisticated three rooms and one screen wall (San Fang Yi Zhao Bi) and four courtyards and five patios (Si He Wu Tian Jing) layouts. A standout feature is the Shining Wall (Zhaobi), designed to reflect the soft afternoon plateau light back into the courtyard. These structures are built with intricate tenon-and-mortise wooden frames, a flexible engineering feat that has allowed them to survive centuries of seismic activity.",
